# Project Development Roadmap

## Phase 1 – Research & Planning

**Objective:** Define the project scope and finalize the system architecture.

* Define the project objectives.
* Review literature on sensorless BLDC motor control.
* Study Kalman Filter and Adaptive Kalman Filter theory.
* Understand BLDC motor operation and commutation.
* Select the control strategy.
* Freeze the hardware architecture.
* Create the system block diagram.
* Create the project repository and documentation.

**Deliverables**

* Project specification
* System architecture
* Initial documentation

---

# Phase 2 – Hardware Selection

**Objective:** Select all hardware components required for the project.

* Select STM32 microcontroller.
* Select BLDC motor.
* Select gate driver ICs.
* Select MOSFETs.
* Select current sensing method.
* Select voltage sensing method.
* Select power supply.
* Prepare Bill of Materials (BOM).

**Deliverables**

* Finalized hardware list
* Component datasheets
* Cost estimation

---

# Phase 3 – Inverter Design

**Objective:** Design and build a three-phase inverter.

* Study three-phase inverter topology.
* Design one half-bridge.
* Design gate driver circuits.
* Design bootstrap circuitry.
* Select gate resistors.
* Select DC bus capacitors.
* Build inverter on perfboard.
* Perform continuity and safety checks.

**Deliverables**

* Working inverter hardware
* Wiring documentation

---

# Phase 4 – Power Stage Testing

**Objective:** Verify the inverter before connecting the motor.

* Verify gate driver operation.
* Verify PWM output.
* Test one MOSFET.
* Test one half-bridge.
* Test complete inverter.
* Verify dead-time operation.
* Test with a low-voltage supply.

**Deliverables**

* Functional inverter
* Oscilloscope verification

---

# Phase 5 – Sensor Integration

**Objective:** Integrate current and voltage sensing.

* Install current sensors.
* Install voltage sensing circuit.
* Interface sensors with STM32 ADC.
* Calibrate ADC readings.
* Validate sensor measurements.

**Deliverables**

* Stable current measurements
* Stable voltage measurements

---

# Phase 6 – STM32 Firmware Development

**Objective:** Develop the embedded firmware.

* Configure STM32CubeMX.
* Configure GPIO.
* Configure PWM timers.
* Configure ADC.
* Configure interrupts.
* Configure UART for debugging.
* Verify PWM generation.
* Verify ADC acquisition.

**Deliverables**

* Working firmware framework

---

# Phase 7 – Basic Motor Control

**Objective:** Achieve controlled BLDC motor operation.

* Implement six-step commutation.
* Generate phase PWM.
* Verify motor rotation.
* Test different duty cycles.
* Verify current measurements during operation.

**Deliverables**

* Stable motor operation

---

# Phase 8 – Mathematical Modeling

**Objective:** Develop the mathematical model of the BLDC motor.

* Determine motor parameters.
* Develop electrical model.
* Develop mechanical model.
* Derive state-space equations.
* Validate the model through simulation.

**Deliverables**

* State-space model
* Motor parameters

---

# Phase 9 – Standard Kalman Filter

**Objective:** Implement a baseline Kalman Filter.

* Define system states.
* Define system matrices.
* Implement prediction step.
* Implement correction step.
* Validate estimation accuracy.

**Deliverables**

* Working Kalman Filter

---

# Phase 10 – Adaptive Kalman Filter

**Objective:** Upgrade the estimator.

* Implement adaptive noise covariance estimation.
* Tune adaptive parameters.
* Evaluate convergence.
* Test under varying operating conditions.

**Deliverables**

* Working Adaptive Kalman Filter

---

# Phase 11 – Closed-Loop Sensorless Control

**Objective:** Integrate estimation with motor control.

* Use estimated rotor position for commutation.
* Eliminate dependence on Hall sensors.
* Verify sensorless startup.
* Test under different speeds and loads.

**Deliverables**

* Functional sensorless BLDC control

---

# Phase 12 – Validation & Performance Evaluation

**Objective:** Evaluate system performance.

* Compare estimated and actual rotor position.
* Evaluate estimation error.
* Measure computational execution time.
* Measure CPU utilization.
* Evaluate robustness to parameter variation.
* Test repeatability.

**Deliverables**

* Experimental results
* Performance analysis

---

# Phase 13 – Documentation

**Objective:** Complete project documentation.

* Update GitHub repository.
* Prepare project report.
* Create system diagrams.
* Record demonstration videos.
* Prepare presentation.
* Document future work.

**Deliverables**

* Complete project documentation
* Final report
* Presentation
